<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">317</span> - <span property="pageEnd">333</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16549600/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16549600</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.262055068">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ALCAPA+%3D+anomalous+origin+of+the+coronary+artery+from+the+pulmonary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ALCAPA = anomalous origin of the coronary artery from the pulmonary artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ECG+%3D+electrocardiographically&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ECG = electrocardiographically</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=LAD+%3D+left+anterior+descending&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">LAD = left anterior descending</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=LCA+%3D+left+main+coronary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">LCA = left main coronary artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=LCx+%3D+left+circumflex&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">LCx = left circumflex</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PDA+%3D+posterior+descending+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PDA = posterior descending artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=RCA+%3D+right+coronary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">RCA = right coronary artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=VR+%3D+volume+rendered&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">VR = volume rendered</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The multi-detector row CT manifestations and clinical significance of various coronary artery anomalies of origin, course, and termination are discussed and illustrated, and findings at CT are correlated with angiographic findings.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">So Yeon</span> <span property="familyName">Kim</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span p